		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Kingdom of Spain is a country in SouthWest Europe on the Iberian Peninsula. It shares a border with Portugal to the West, France to the North East, and Morocco to the South across the Straight of Gibraltar. Spain also has two archipelagos (group of islands) the Canary Islands of the coast of Northern Africa, and the Balearic Islands in the Mediterranean Sea.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://cdn.getyourguide.com/img/location/5df35e14ce3f3.jpeg/88.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Canary Islands, Spain</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Findings of modern humans in Spain date back 35,000 years. The Iberian Peninsula was occupied by many different cultures. The Phoenicians arrived in the 9th century BC, followed by the Greeks, then the Carthaginians until the Romans arrived in 200 BC. At the end of the Roman Empire, the Visigoths took over the land until the Islamic Moors arrived from Northern Africa in the 8th century AD, and controlled the area for several hundred years. The Moors left a small pocket of Christians near the Pyrenées out of the Muslim rule. Over the
course for 700 years, this small pocket of Christians grew into small Kingdoms, and expanded South. In 1479 the Kingdom of Spain was formed when Isabel and Ferdinand became King and Queen of Spain by uniting two Kingdoms.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://i2.wp.com/ribalych.ru/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/1652.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Moorish people greatly influenced Spanish culture and architecture (Alhambra Citadel, Granada)</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				In the 1500s, during the Age of Exploration, Spain became the most powerful country in the world. Spanish conquistadores Hernan Cortes and Francisco Pizarro conquered most of the Americas and claimed them for Spain. Continued wars started the decline of Spain. In 1800s most of Spains colonies started to revolt against Spain and separated. In 1898 after losing the Spanish-American war, they lost many of the colonies in the Americas. In 1936 Spain had a civil war, which was won by General Francisco Franco who ruled the country until 1975 as a dictator. Spain was not in World War II, but somewhat tied to Germany which created some issues for Spain later on. In 1976 constitutional democracy was established in Spain in the form of parliamentary constitutional monarchy, with the King as head of state. Today Spain is a major developed country with a high income economy. It is a member of the European Union, and the Schengen Area.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Spain is divided into 17 autonomous communities which effectively govern themselves. Spain is also a land of distinctive cultures of Catalan, Galician and Basque whose people retain their own language, culture and customs.
Geography of Spain is mountainous with many mountain ranges like the Pyrenees, and the Sierra Nevada mountains with Mulhacén, the highest point, at 3,400 meters (11,400 feet).

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.chilloutdoor.es/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Winteractivities-Spanish-Pyrenees-Chill-Outdoor.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Pyrenees mountains, northeastern Spain</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Climate of Spain differs with regions. The Northern part of Spain is green and moist. Central Spain is a dry and dusty plateau known as the Meseta. Andalusia region in the South is a hot and dry land of red soil, cactuses, olive groves and white washed villages.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Spain is known for its fiestas(parties), siestas(nap times taken right after lunch), and Flamenco (a passionate music and dance style).
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Spain has been dominated by football since the early 20th century. Spain’s beloved teams like Real Madrid CF, and FC Barcelona are two of the worlds most successful football teams. Also Spanish National Team won many European Championships as well as the World Cup in 2010.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
